{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Appoint a Children and Young People\u2019s Domestic Abuse Commissioner (0 to 25 yrs)",
        "additional_details": "1 in 5 UK children live with domestic abuse. Despite the 2021 Act, young victims are being re-traumatized by a system that mislabels their trauma as \"bad behavior\" or \"perpetration.\" There is a \u00a3232m shortfall in specialist services, leaving children in refuges and care without emotional support. Care leavers (18-25) face a \"cliff edge\" of homelessness and unprocessed trauma. I want a Commissioner to stop the criminalization of trauma and ensure ring-fenced funding to break the cycle.",
        "background": "I call on the Government to appoint a dedicated Domestic Abuse Commissioner for Children and Young People. To ensure  accountability, ring-fenced funding, and specialist trauma-informed support for all young victims\u2014including those still in the home, in refuge, in care, or care leavers up to age 25.",
